  <sect2>
    <title>Installation</title>

    <para>
      HTML Tidy tarballs are no longer generated by the maintainers. To obtain
      the source code, check out the HTML Tidy CVS repository:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>cvs -d:pserver:anonymous@tidy.cvs.sourceforge.net:/cvsroot/tidy co -P tidy &amp;&amp;
cd tidy</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Install HTML Tidy by running the following commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>sh build/gnuauto/setup.sh &amp;&amp;
./configure --prefix=/usr \
            --disable-static &amp;&amp;
make</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Now, as the <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>

  <sect2>
    <title>Configuration</title>

    <para>
      The default configuration options can be set in the file defined in
      <envar>$HTML_TIDY</envar>. Additional configuration options can be passed
      to <command>tidy</command> via command line parameters or the
      <option>-config &lt;file&gt;</option> parameter.
    </para>

  </sect2>

